The paper presents an approach to solving the problem of picking up, transporting, and dropping off novel objects outdoors using a mobile manipulator. This involves integrating a navigation system, a grasp detection and planning system, and a custom task planner. The paper focuses on the robotics aspect of the system, making cs.RO the most likely sub-category. However, the system also involves computer vision (grasp detection) and artificial intelligence (task planning), making cs.CV and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The system's success rate is also mentioned, indicating a possible focus on machine learning, which would make cs.LG a likely sub-category. Finally, the system involves control and decision-making, which could make cs.SY a possible sub-category.
